public class ZipFileInputCursor<E>
extends InputStreamCursor<E>

This class provides a cursor that reads the input from an entry of a given zip file.

Constructor Detail

ZipFileInputCursor

public ZipFileInputCursor(Converter<? extends E> converter,
                          java.io.File file,
                          java.lang.String zipEntry,
                          int bufferSize)
Constructs a new zip-file-input cursor that depends on the specified zip file and uses the specified converter in order to read out the serialized objects from the given zip entry.

Parameters:
converter - the converter that is used for reading out the serialized objects of this iteration.
file - the zip file that contains the serialized objects of this iteration.
zipEntry - the name of the entry inside the zip file containing the data of the iteration.
bufferSize - the size of the buffer that is used for the file input.

ZipFileInputCursor

public ZipFileInputCursor(Converter<? extends E> converter,
                          java.io.File file,
                          java.lang.String zipEntry)
Constructs a new zip-file-input cursor that depends on the specified zip file and uses the specified converter in order to read out the serialized objects from the given zip entry. The buffer size is set to 4096 bytes.

Parameters:
converter - the converter that is used for reading out the serialized objects of this iteration.
file - the zip file that contains the serialized objects of this iteration.
zipEntry - the name of the entry inside the zip file containing the data of the iteration.
